This paper is primarily focused on recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses privacy concerns related to the release of user data, which falls under the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of anonymization techniques to protect user privacy is related to database systems (cs.DB) and the use of data mining techniques to extract useful information from anonymized data is related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
